summary: aziraphale wears glasses just for the aesthetic and crowley never once calls him on it because he is sort of fond of...
body:
aziraphale wears glasses just for the aesthetic and crowley never once calls him on it because he is sort of fond of aziraphale’s aesthetic in this world weary way like what are you wearing angel but doesn’t actually want aziraphale to change it at all

but after the armageddon that wasn’t, one night when they’re sharing a bit of wine and reminiscing about this or that, aziraphale reaches out and snags crowley’s sunglasses off. i just want to see you properly, aziraphale says. 

crowley huffs, pretending to be put upon. you can have mine if i can have yours. 

to which aziraphale laughs. it’s not the same! i need mine to see! 

and crowley, in absolute awe at this total moron he’s fallen in love with, who has apparently forgotten that he doesn’t actually need the glasses, says, aziraphale, you’re a bloody angel. you don’t even need eyes to see. 

and aziraphale says, oh, and then, oh, and then, grinning, come here then so i can see you properly with my hands.

and crowley thinks that is a terrible line, probably the worst line he’s heard in six thousand years, but he grins back, and he goes.
